claim.claim-text:
14. A non-transitory computer readable medium having sets of instructions stored thereon, which when executed by a processor cause the processor to:
store data for a plurality of brokerage accounts held by a broker, wherein the data includes updated information for each of the brokerage accounts based on account activity;
analyze the account information contained in each of the brokerage accounts to identify a set of the brokerage accounts meeting criteria for performing margin loan securitization;
flag accounts with which to perform margin loan securitization;
segregate securities supporting margin loans held in flagged accounts such that the securities cannot be rehypothecated; and
securitize the margin loans of the flagged accounts, wherein securitizing comprises initiating a transfer of the margin loans from the broker.
